The paper deals with integrating learning and motion planning for soccer playing robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bayesian optimisation and k-Nearest Neighbour approach for trajectory optimisation and reuse of prior information suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions velocity profiling, which could involve machine learning techniques and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the testing of the developed simulator and physical robots could involve computer vision techniques for tracking and analysis, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
